From: Norman Ronald <n-ronald@TVMDL.TAMU.EDU>
The Associate Diagnostic Knowledge Base for Infectious and Parasitic
Diseases of Man indicates that the encephalopathy occurring in the two
children in the Congo is most likely due to an enterovirus which has
disseminated to the brain.
